MedSearch is an open-science tool for searching the medical and scientific
literature. It queries public and subscription literature sources on the user's
behalf and does not redistribute their content; all article data belongs to its
respective publishers and providers (including, among others, PubMed/NCBI,
Cochrane, ClinicalTrials.gov, arXiv, Scopus/Elsevier, Web of Science/Clarivate,
Unpaywall, and OpenAlex). Use of those services is subject to their own terms.

This software builds on open-source components, including Flask, pywebview, and
rumps, each distributed under its own permissive license.
